      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/49/3",
      "text": [
        " : سَأَلْتُ أَبَا عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ عَنِ اَلرَّجُلِ يُعْتِقُ اَلرَّجُلَ فِي كَفَّارَةِ يَمِينٍ أَوْ ظِهَارٍ لِمَنْ يَكُونُ اَلْوَلاَءُ قَالَ \"لِلَّذِي أَعْتَقَ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3496 - It is narrated from Asim ibn Humayd, from Abu Basir, who said:\nI asked Abu Abdullah (as), about a man who frees another man as an expiation for breaking an oath or for zihar (a prohibited declaration regarding one's wife).\nImam (as) said: \"The wala' (bond of loyalty) belongs to the one who freed him.\""
        ]
      }
    },
